Section 1:
1 L.D. 1604
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 ENVIRONMENT AND NATURAL RESOURCES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 641, L.D. 1604, “An Act to Protect
10 Groundwater and Surface Waters from Perfluoroalkyl and Polyfluoroalkyl Substances
11 from Landfill Leachate”
12 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2.
13 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 4 and inserting the following:
14 'Sec. 4. 38 MRSA §1310-N, sub-§10-A is enacted to read:
15 10-A. Testing of landfill leachate for perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl
16 substances. In accordance with a schedule approved by the department, a solid waste
17 landfill that collects and manages leachate shall integrate into the landfill's department-
18 approved water quality monitoring plan the sampling and analysis of leachate for
19 perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances. A solid waste landfill shall provide the
20 results from leachate testing conducted pursuant to this subsection to the department in
21 accordance with the landfill's department-approved water quality monitoring plan and as
22 part of the landfill's annual report. On an annual basis, the department shall make results
23 from leachate testing conducted by solid waste landfills pursuant to this subsection
24 available on its publicly accessible website.'
25 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 5 and inserting the following:
26 'Sec. 5. 38 MRSA §1310-N, sub-§10-B is enacted to read:
27 10-B. Testing of private water supplies for perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl
28 substances. Upon written request to the department from the owner of a property abutting
29 a solid waste landfill that collects and manages leachate, the department shall require the
30 landfill to conduct a one-time sampling and analysis for perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl
31 substances of a private water supply well used by the owner for drinking water purposes.
32 If the analysis indicates possible perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances
33 contamination of the private water supply well from the solid waste landfill, the department
34 shall require the solid waste landfill to conduct additional sampling and analysis of the
35 private water supply well for perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances in a manner
Page 1 - 132LR1669(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 641, L.D. 1604
316 directed by the department. For purposes of this subsection, a property is considered to be
327 abutting a solid waste landfill if the property is contiguous to property on which the landfill
338 is located, including directly across a public or private right-of-way from the landfill, and
349 is located within one mile of property on which the landfill is located.
5 A. Sampling and analysis for perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances pursuant
6 to this subsection must be conducted in accordance with procedures outlined in the
7 solid waste landfill's department-approved water quality monitoring plan.
8 B. The laboratory performing the sampling and analysis pursuant to this subsection
9 shall provide written copies of the results to the solid waste landfill, the property owner
10 and the department.'
11 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
12 number to read consecutively.
13 SUMMARY
1144 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, amends the bill to
1155 remove the provision prohibiting, beginning June 1, 2026, a licensed wastewater discharger
1166 from discharging any wastewater containing leachate collected from a solid waste landfill
1177 unless the effluent discharged satisfies limits adopted by the Department of Environmental
1188 Protection by rule regarding the amount of perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances
1199 in effluent discharges. The amendment also makes clarifying changes to the provision of
2200 the bill requiring a solid waste landfill to test landfill leachate for perfluoroalkyl and
2211 polyfluoroalkyl substances and to the provision of the bill requiring a solid waste landfill
2222 to test a private water supply well for perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances if
2233 directed by the department upon the request of an abutting property owner.
2244 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2255 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR1669(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
